##### •	We then enter a loop that runs from k=1 to k=n*n
##### •	In each iteration of the loop, we do the following:We set the value of the current cell to k
##### •	We check if the next cell in the direction of (di, dj) is already filled
##### •	If it is, we change the direction of motion by swapping di and dj and negating the new value of dj
##### •	We update the values of i and j by adding di and dj respectively
##### •	After the loop completes, we return the filled matrix
