**Total number of iteration** through the matrix to get all the elements in spiral order is : **"K= (n*2)-1 "**
where **n : number of rows** (or *number of colums* as the matrix is **n *x* n**)

This formula can be understood by taking example of 3x3 *(5 iterations)*, 4x4 *(7 iterations)* , 5x5 *(9 iterations)* .... matrix (just to get the idea).
We are basically iterating in the four directions through the matrix.
i.e. 
*1)left to right in a particular row (i.e. iterating through columns in a particular row)
2)up to bottom in the particular column (i.e. iterating through rows in a particular column)
3)right to left in the particular row (i.e. iterating through columns in a particular row)
4)bottom to up in the particular column (i.e. iterating through rows in a particular column)*

```

class Solution {
    public int[][] generateMatrix(int n) {
        int[][] matrix = new int[n][n];
        int c=0,r=1,k=(n*2)-1;
        while (c<k){
            for (int j = c; j < n; ++j) {
                matrix[c][j]=r;
                ++r;
            }
            for (int i = c +1; i <n; ++i) {
                matrix[i][n-1]=r;
                ++r;
            }
            for (int j = n-2; j >= c; --j) {
                matrix[n-1][j]=r;
                ++r;
            }
            for (int i = n-2; i > c; --i) {
                matrix[i][c]=r;
                ++r;
            }
            --n;
            ++c;
        }
        return matrix;
    }
}
